The paper deals with algorithmic information theory and coding, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of random oracles and the concept of randomness also suggest a connection to cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the use of data structures, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS). Finally, the optimization of redundancy in coding suggests a connection to machine learning and data compression (cs.LG).
